      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POPPY'S FOX (6) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish 1.75 lengths away in third (16.36) behind Vinnie Zacapa at this track. Has good speed so he should be prominent despite the draw. Can measure up this time. KALANI CHRIS (8) has finished in the money in each of his three runs so far, the latest when second (23.33) at this track. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Looks one of the leading chances again. PROJECT NEMESIS (2) comes off an average performance last start when fifth at this track over 400m behind Blazing Biscuit (23.38) in a Maiden. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Can measure up this time. TIGER KEY CHUM (1) missed the placings here most recently but can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
